# MDP traceability

Milestones and issues in **~/work/ai-coordinate/coordinate-planner** must trace back to the coordinate repo’s requirements and solution docs.

## Source docs

- **Requirements**: `docs/01-requirements/` (vision, stakeholders, goals, personas, functional/NFR, scope, assumptions, risks, glossary).
- **Solution**: `docs/02-solution/` (overview, architecture, data model, API, UI/UX, tech stack, security, integration, infra, testing).

## Linking work to docs

- When creating or updating an issue, reference the specific doc(s) in the issue body or description (e.g. "Source: docs/01-requirements/01-vision.md").
- Milestones align to phases: M-1 Problem & alignment, M-2 User/scope freeze, M-3 Risk gate, M-4 Solution baseline, M-5 Delivery readiness.

## Acceptance criteria and checklists

- Keep acceptance criteria and checklist items **concrete and testable** (e.g. "Glossary has at least 5 defined terms" or "Architecture diagram matches C4 level 1").
- Use `mdp issue update --add-checklist "item"` and `mdp issue update --check "item"` to track completion.
